From: Chris Kohn <chris.kohn@amd.com>
Subject: [PATCH] rosbag2_py: Fix pybind11 module extension suffix for cross-compilation

When cross-compiling, pybind11 uses the native Python's extension suffix
(e.g., .cpython-312-x86_64-linux-gnu.so) instead of the target
architecture. This causes the generated modules to have incorrect names
that Python cannot import on the target.

Override PYTHON_MODULE_EXTENSION using PYTHON_SOABI (passed by Yocto via
-DPYTHON_SOABI=cpython-312-aarch64-linux-gnu) when cross-compiling.

AI-Generated: Claude claude-opus-4-6
Signed-off-by: Chris Kohn <chris.kohn@amd.com>

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -35,6 +35,12 @@ find_package(rosbag2_transport REQUIRED)
 # Find python before pybind11
 find_package(Python3 REQUIRED COMPONENTS Interpreter Development)

+# When cross-compiling, override the Python module extension suffix
+# The native Python returns x86_64-linux-gnu but we need aarch64-linux-gnu
+if(CMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING AND DEFINED PYTHON_SOABI)
+  set(PYTHON_MODULE_EXTENSION ".${PYTHON_SOABI}.so")
+endif()
+
 find_package(pybind11_vendor REQUIRED)
 find_package(pybind11 REQUIRED)

